nated  for  the  simple  reason  that  we  believe  it  may  be  wiser  to  approach  the  seat 
as  part  of  an  integrated  unit  rather  than  treat  it  as  a  separate  part.’’  Jeff  Plungis, 
$106  Million  Judgment  Against  Chrysler  and  New  Safety  Studies  Intensify  the  De-
bate  Over  Federal  Standards,  DETROIT NEWS,  Dec.  19.  2004.  This  is  what  NHTSA 
proposed  to  do  in  1974.  It  appears  that  the  agency  has  dragged  its  feet  hardly  an 
inch in three decades. 

